===Adjective===
'''anthropophilic'''
#'''anthropophilic''' (an·thro·po·phil·ic) (an²thr[schwa]-po-fil¢ik) [anthropo- + -philic]  means preferring human beings to other animals, such as a mosquito or a dermatophyte [http://www.mercksource.com/pp/us/cns/cns_hl_dorlands.jspzQzpgzEzzSzppdocszSzuszSzcommonzSzdorlandszSzdorlandzSzdmd_a_46zPzhtm]. It is especially alluding to: 1) bloodsucking arthropods, denoting the preference of a parasite for the human host  as a source of blood or tissues over an animal host; and 2) dermatophytic fungi which grow preferentially on humans [http://www.biology-online.org/dictionary/anthropophilic].